The paper deals with Linear Programming (LP) decoding of Low-Density-Parity-Check (LDPC) codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves discrete steps and finding equidistant configurations, which suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DC). The paper also involves optimization (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI) aspects, as it deals with error-correction schemes and Signal-to-Noise-Ratios (SNR).
